{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"rebar-debug Phase 1 (Gather) — dossier + leading hypothesis:\n\nClaimed + working in worktree ../rebar-flaky-head off origin/main. This is a CHRONIC bug: prior fix edf7 (vocal-dip-robin, commit 2271912cc 'retry transient git object-DB failure on git add') confirmed the class as a transient runner-FS fault (git add failing to create a loose-object temp under the tracker's shared .git/objects/, ENOENT Linux / EINVAL macOS) and added a 3x retry — but ONLY on event_append._git_add (the CREATE path). The recurrence is on the TRANSITION path.\n\nLeading hypothesis (to confirm): the transition/claim git ops run through _git() -> run_git_write() (src/rebar/_commands/txn.py:117-128, calls at 267-268 STATUS and 379-380 CLAIM). run_git_write (gitutil) self-heals ONLY git index.lock contention, NOT the transient object-DB signature that event_append._git_add retries. So the same transient FS fault that edf7 fixed for CREATE hits the transition path's 'git add'/'git commit' UNPROTECTED and surfaces as the hard StoreError 'git operation failed: fatal: could not parse HEAD' (exit 2, txn.py:128). i.e. edf7's fix was incomplete — it left the txn.py transition/claim path un-retried. NOTE edf7 wrongly assumed 'xdist absent -> serial'; CI runs -n 4 --dist worksteal.\n\nRunning now: 3 parallel investigators (code-tracer: exact git mechanism for 'could not parse HEAD' + retry-gap; concurrency/empirical: any hidden concurrency or shared object-DB across xdist workers, unborn-HEAD timing, gc; historical: edf7 fix scope + full git-op call-site retry-coverage table + sibling unprotected sites) + a best-effort local repro loop (edf7 could NOT repro locally: 0/50 isolated, 0/200 saturated, 6/6 clean full-suite — so a local RED may be infeasible)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784232336245328001,"uuid":"fe722ffc-68f1-4496-a024-e008f9cf53e9"}